You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for SSH key operations.

SSH-KEY COMMANDS
  add:         Add an SSH key to your GitHub account
  list:        Lists SSH keys in your GitHub account
  delete:      Delete an SSH key from your GitHub account


Note: These commands manage SSH keys for your GitHub account globally and do not require the --repo flag.

Example usage:
- List keys: GH_PAGER="" gh ssh-key list
- Add key: GH_PAGER="" gh ssh-key add <key-file> --title "My Key"
- Delete key: GH_PAGER="" gh ssh-key delete <key-id> 